&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Hi Bruce,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; in fact one has to be cautious as to &quot;false positives&quot; when using this
&gt; &gt; method, especially for 1-syllable words like &quot;(h)ear, &quot;air&quot; and &quot;I&quot;. Some
&gt; of
&gt; &gt; the SpeakJet allophones are diphthongs, e.g. #22 (&quot;IYRR&quot; like in &quot;Clear,
&gt; &gt; Hear, Year&quot;), #23 (&quot;EYRR&quot; like in &quot;Hair, Stair, Repair&quot;), or #30 (&quot;OHIH&quot;
&gt; &gt; like in &quot;Sky, Five, I&quot;). There are only 72 different allophones, so the
&gt; &gt; probability that one-syllable words like &quot;(h)ear/here&quot; , &quot;air&quot;, and &quot;I&quot;
&gt; &gt; appear, is relatively high.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I don&#39;t assume that everything that is received by this method is true
&gt; &gt; communication. As with every method, it depends on various factors like
&gt; &gt; meaningfulness, relatedness, length of the message, etc., if a message is
&gt; &gt; regarded as a valid EVP.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Stefan
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; ----- original Nachricht --------
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Betreff: [EVP-ITC] EVP Maker (allaphone file) Method Test
&gt; &gt; Gesendet: Do, 03. Apr 2008
&gt; &gt; Von: bhali333&lt;paranormalinvestigating@...&gt;
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; To all that are experimenting with the EVPM allaphone file method.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; I have done a few sessions with this method as I know a  few other 
&gt; &gt; &gt; researchers have.
&gt; &gt; &gt; There have been a couple of researchers that have done sessions and 
&gt; &gt; &gt; gotten very similar responses such as the name &quot;Arthur&quot; and responses 
&gt; &gt; &gt; pertaining to &quot;Air&quot; also &quot;I am here&quot; or &quot;here&quot;.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; I have also gotten direct and intelligible answers to questions 
&gt; &gt; &gt; immediately following the question, and messages that could never be 
&gt; &gt; &gt; construed as random.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; The test that I propose and the answer I seek is, The words that keep 
&gt; &gt; &gt; coming up to almost all researchers experimenting with this method IE 
&gt; &gt; &gt; the words I mentioned above.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; I would like to find out whether these certain words are simply by 
&gt; &gt; &gt; products of everyone using the same file and come up as a result of 
&gt; &gt; &gt; the file playing in evpm, or are they true entity communication.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; The only questionable content are these few words not all the methods 
&gt; &gt; &gt; communication. In my opinion the majority of the communication from 
&gt; &gt; &gt; this method is genuine.
&gt; &gt; &gt; The method has produced communication including my name to me as well 
&gt; &gt; &gt; as other researchers that have gotten my name, and some of the 
&gt; &gt; &gt; statements and responses show signs of a sense of humor that would 
&gt; &gt; &gt; surely be absent in random word grouping.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Who ever is involved with experimentation of this method, will you 
&gt; &gt; &gt; please on your next session ask that if there is a spirit named 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Arthur for him not to mention his name or the list of words that I 
&gt; &gt; &gt; have posted. I suggest that this request be made verbally before the 
&gt; &gt; &gt; session as well as after.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; And in the most polite manner. They seem to respond better to 
&gt; &gt; &gt; formality.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; please dedicate one session no shorter than 2 minutes to this 
&gt; &gt; &gt; experiment and post your results.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Your cooperation appreciated.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Bruce
